result.execSummary:
The defendant Linzey C Woods was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Carry Concealed Weapon, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.23(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: REQUEST TO ISSUE CIVIL JUDGMENT FOR RESTITUTION RECEIVED AND FORWARDED TO ALI. OS

Defendant Linzey C Woods in court with attorney Leah R. Thomas.  Defendant Linzey C Woods in custody.  Chad Wozniak appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
BRANCH 45 for BRANCH 24
As to Count 1:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the Defendant guilty and enters judgment of conviction into the record forthwith. 

As to Count 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on State's motion, Court orders Count 2 DISMISSED but read-in as to sentencing.

Sentencing Proceeded. Statements by parties and defendant.  

The court sentenced the defendant to 4.5 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 49 days time served, with Huber privileges for work and school.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 18 months with the following conditions:  

-Obtain/maintain full time employment/school.
-Obtain GED/HSED. Enroll by 7-09-2015.
-Perform 30 hours of community service. 
-Cognitive behavior therapy.
-No contact with Javon Cook. 
-No use/possession of any weapons or firearms. 
-No violent contact at all with anyone.
-Pay all costs, fees and surcharges at the rate of $25.00 per month with the first payment due on 07-29-2015 and additional payments due the 29th of each month thereafter.  If there are any missed payments any remaining balance will be due FORTHWITH and an immediate entry of a civil judgment is ordered by the court.
